  fat: 20.2 g
  saturated fat: 1.9 g
  carbohydrates: 84.5 g
  sugar: 13.6 g
  protein: 31.5 g
  sodium: 2 g
  serving size: 503
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipes/hake-and-golden-rice-6447ebd2b3e6d9a85fbc344f
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Pour @water{300%ml}(cold salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g}, @Hello Muscat{1%sachet} and @ground turmeric{1%sachet} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower heat to medium, cover and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Trim the @carrot{1} and quarter lengthways. Chop into small pieces. (no need to peel).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

Pat the @hake{250%g} dry with #kitchen paper{}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Place a #pan{} over high heat (without @oil{to taste}).

When hot, fry the carrot, onion and pepper until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once cooked, season with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Add the veg to the pot of rice.

Use a #fork{} to mix it all together, fluffing up the rice as you go. Cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, lay the fish into the pan and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn over and cook on the other side for a further ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish. Fish is cooked when opaque in the centre.

With ~{1%minute} left to cook, add @butter{2%tbsp}, @dried thyme{1%sachet} and lemon zest to the pan.

Once melted, use a #spoon{} to baste the fish with the lemony butter.

Loosen the @aioli{1%sachet} with a squeeze of lemon juice.

Taste and add more if desired, you want the aioli to be a drizzling consistency.

Divide the savoury golden rice between plates or #bowls{}.

Top with the pan-fried hake, pouring over any butter remaining in the pan.

Finish with a drizzle of the lemon aioli.